# Agent Windows test workflow

## Do not guess WinUI3 fixes

Before editing manifests, host bootstrap, or register scripts, read **`docs/windows-winui3-method.md`**, **`docs/windows-winui3-restore-layers.md`**, and **`docs/WINUI3-CHANGELOG.md`**. Default **`WINUI3_LAYER=hello`** (`cf233c0`).

Required: `git diff f9bad4e` on launch-critical files, read `build-win/winui3-debug.log`, match log strings to `git show f9bad4e` / `d801516` source. One layer per change. Append changelog. Do not toggle `PackageDependency`, arch, or `OnPackageIdentity_NOOP` from memory.

**Split:** agent compiles, trusts cert, registers sparse MSIX, and runs the demo over SSH; user only runs the `.exe` locally if they want to see the UI.

## Directories (Windows `snappr-win`)

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `C:\msys64\tmp\vala.win32\` | Rsync mirror of Linux repo (sources + scripts) |
| `C:\msys64\tmp\vala-win32-build-win\` | Meson/ninja objects (always on C:, not Samba) |
| `C:\msys64\tmp\vala.win32\build-win\` | Shipped demos + DLLs + logs for the user to run |

Do **not** use Samba `X:` for builds or WinUI3 testing. User runs exes from **`C:\msys64\tmp\vala.win32\build-win\`**.

## After changing WinUI3 / build scripts

On Linux git host:

```bash
./scripts/agent-remote-build.sh
```

This: rsync → remote `./scripts/build-win.sh` → **`agent-remote-winui3-setup.ps1`** (cert + `Add-AppxPackage` over SSH) → optional demo run → pulls `build-win/` back to Linux.

Do **not** ask the user to run `certutil` or `Add-AppxPackage` — use `./scripts/agent-remote-build.sh setup` or `build` instead.

Read failures from `build-win/last-build.log` and `build-win/agent-winui3-setup.log`. Do not ask the user to paste logs if pull succeeded.

Subcommands: `build` (full), `setup` (cert+register only), `run` (setup+demo+log pull), `pull`, `validate`.

## User instructions

After build, read **`build-win/YOUR-TASKS.txt`** — should only mention optional local UI run. Agent prints this after every `build` / `validate` / `pull`.

**Method:** **`docs/windows-winui3-method.md`** · **Changelog:** **`docs/WINUI3-CHANGELOG.md`** · **HRESULT layers:** **`docs/windows-winui3-status.md`**

Setup reference: **`docs/windows-winui3.md`**. Checks: `WINUI3-VALIDATION.txt` (does not prove exe launch).

Do not claim WinUI3 is working until `winui3-widgets-native.exe` launches without SxS and log shows package identity.

## Prerequisites

Windows needs MSYS2 `rsync`: see `docs/windows-build.md` § Rsync. SSH host: `snappr-win` (`AGENT_WIN_HOST` to override).
